This clarifies the target spacing and typography.

For the **no-sales-point** screen, the left content should be positioned higher, but not directly under the header. The design looks roughly like:

* Icon: `112 × 112px`
* Space below icon: about `28–32px`
* Title: Ubuntu Bold, `48px`
* Space below title: about `40–48px`
* Body: Open Sans Light, `18px`
* Strong body: Open Sans Bold, `18px`
* Content width: around `680px`

Use this for the left side:

```css
.failure-content {
    padding:
        clamp(56px, 7vh, 84px)
        clamp(32px, 7vw, 120px)
        48px;

    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: flex-start;

    text-align: center;
}
```

Then use these element styles:

```css
.failure-icon {
    width: 112px;
    height: 112px;
    margin: 0 0 32px;
    object-fit: contain;
}

.failure-content h1 {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 0 44px;

    font-family: 'Ubuntu', Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 48px;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;

    color: var(--color-black);
}

.message {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 0 12px;

    font-family: 'Open Sans', Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.45;

    color: var(--color-black);
    text-align: left;
}

.strong-message {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0;

    font-family: 'Open Sans', Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.45;

    color: var(--color-black);
    text-align: left;
}
```

One important point: your current `.failure-content` centers all text. In the design, the icon and title are centered, but the two paragraph blocks are left-aligned. So the paragraph rules should keep:

```css
text-align: left;
```

while the parent remains:

```css
text-align: center;
```

For the technical-error version, the same layout works; only the icon and text change.
